<dl id="n08055f"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n08" href="#n08055f">N08 (VI.B.6)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n08all.htm#n08055f"> 55(f)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> ~ fountain pen ~ <small>Red</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n08055f"><li>FW 563.06 </li><li><a href="../../flex/s/lexs.htm#n08055f">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/s/l39s.htm#n08055f">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n08055f">MS BL 47485-31</ms> </li><li>JJA 60:259 <a name="sd2" href="../../FF/fdra/sda.htm#sd2">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/s/sd2.htm#n08055f">Draft: III&sect;4.2</a></li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">L&apos;observation des &eacute;critures plates et floues est devenue d&eacute;licate depuis l&apos;usage si r&eacute;pandu des porte-plumes &agrave; r&eacute;servoir, dont les plumes douces, et l&apos;encre fluide, &eacute;paississentuniform&eacute;ment les traits. Tout ce qui touche &agrave; la pression dans l&apos;&eacute;criture a besoin d&apos;&ecirc;tre contr&ocirc;l&eacute;, v&eacute;rifi&eacute; sur plusieurs documents. <br><font color="green">[The study of flat and indistinct writing has become more difficult with the widespread use of fountain pens with soft nibs, and flowing ink, that give a uniform thickness to each stroke. Everything concerning pressure in writing needs to be checked, verified by means of several documents.]</font> <small> J Cr&eacute;pieux-Jamin, <a name="JCJL" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#JCJL"><cite title="source">Les &eacute;l&eacute;ments de l'&eacute;criture des canailles</cite></a> (1923) 220</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
